  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/3893",
  "title": "feat(index): use widget [PART-2]",
  "body": "This PR introduces the usage of the `index` widget through `InstantSearch`. With the previous PR, we saw that the widget is now responsible for managing widgets & state. We now leverage the widget inside `InstantSearch`.\r\n\r\nBy default, all `InstantSearch` instance has a \"main\" index that replaces the logic that was previously inside the instance. The instance exposes functions (like `scheduleXXX`) to be able to manage multiple indices at the same time. The `index` widgets are self-contained and they don't have that much knowledge about the external world. The instance is here to \"sync\" their behavior (like a `render`). The change should be invisible for regular users since the API didn't change.\r\n\r\nWith these changes, I've merged all the tests related to `InstantSearch` inside the same module. I also get rid of a bunch of them because we cover most of them through the `index` widget. Inside the PR I've tried to linked which test is replacing what to ease the review.",
